[Difficulty "advanced"]
[SkillPath "declarer_play/squeeze_plays"]
[Student "S"]
{North is to play 6NT. East leads the \HK.

As usual, you have 11 winners; 3 \Ss, 1 \H, 4 \Ds and 3 \Cs. If \Ss split 3-3 dummy's \S6  will become trick #12. If \Ss don't split though, you will have the chance of a squeeze if the defender with long \Ss also has 4 or more \Cs.

For a squeeze to operate you will need to lose one trick and the time to do that is right now. Let East hold the \HK and win his \H continuation with your \HA. 

West discarded a \D on the second \H.

You might as well find out about the \Ss right now. Play the \S A K Q. 

Too bad, East discards a \H on the third round of \Ss.  

West now holds the the only guard in \Ss.

Play the \DA, then \D K Q. 

West will follow to all three \Ds.  

Now for the squeeze. Play dummy's \DJ and discard your \H10.

If West discards the \SJ you will cash dummy's \S6, then win the last 3 \C tricks. 

So West will no doubt throw a \C instead. In which case you win the last 4 \C tricks.

Squeezes are so very satisfying.}
[Play "W"]HK

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Deal "E:A.J74.AKJ975.A74 KT73.KQT6.32.T95 Q52.A82.Q864.KQ2 J9864.953.T.J863"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "6D"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
1D pass 2NT pass 4D pass 5D pass 6D pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "9fbb1d1410946c5035fcf8785fd2c666d20d9c16d4a89c3fcf3404bec94c890b"]
[Category "Declarer Play"]
[Difficulty "advanced"]
[SkillPath "declarer_play/squeeze_plays"]
[Student "S"]
{East is to play 6\D. South leads the \HK.

You have 11 winners; 1 \S, 1 \H, 6 \Ds and 3 \Cs.

At first things look hopeless, but remember this is a lesson on squeeze plays. From the opening lead you know that South must hold the \HQ. If he also holds the \SK you will be able to squeeze him in \Hs and \Ss.

You let the \HK win, (hoping he will play another \H), but he plays a small trump instead which you win in your hand. 

Pull one more round of trumps, then unblock the \SA.

Then take your 3 \C winners, ending in your hand. 

Now play \DQ, \DJ, \D9. Discard the \S5 from dummy on the third \D.  

[showcards N:SQ,HA,H8 E:SJ,S9,H9 S:HJ,H7,D7 W:SK,HQ,HT]

South could afford to throw 2 \Ss and a \H on your \D plays.

But when you play the \D7 he is squeezed.

He cannot dump his \SK because you would throw the \H8 and dummy would be high.

So he will discard the \H10 instead. At this point you know that the \SQ is worthless so you discard it. You win the final two tricks with the \HA and \HJ.}
[Play "W"]HK

